# Supabase Database

## Migrations

- Sequential naming: `001_initial_schema.sql`, `002_v2_hardening.sql`, …
- Place in `supabase/migrations/`
- Run via Supabase CLI or dashboard SQL editor
- **v2.0 gate:** apply `002_v2_hardening.sql` before soft launch; verify with `python scripts/ff-metrics.py` → `migration_002_ok: true`

## Schema

- `users` — one row per Telegram user (telegram_id unique)
- `game_runs` — every completed session, FK to users
- `submit_cooldowns` (002) — shared 10s rate limit per telegram_id
- `api_sessions` (002) — session tokens for leaderboard highlight; pruned on `/auth/me`

## RLS

- Public SELECT on users and game_runs (leaderboard reads)
- `submit_cooldowns` and `api_sessions` — no public policies (service role only)
- No INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE policies for anon on write tables — API uses service role
- Never add client-side write policies

## Leaderboard Queries

- Daily: `created_at >= date_trunc('day', now() AT TIME ZONE 'UTC')`
- Weekly: `created_at >= now() - interval '7 days'`
- API fetches up to 2000 recent runs, best per user in period, top 50 in Python
